page.title: 07A Typical Day in Woodchurch
page.content: I get up at 7.30.I get dressed.Our uniform is grey and maroon,with a grey and maroon tie.For breakfast I have sugar puffs or shredded wheat.I sometimes have egg and bacon.School starts at 9.00 am.We usully have assembly first.Next our teacher takes the register before lessons begin.Break is at 10.30am -10.45am. We play bulldog ,cricket ,football or rounders.We have lunch at 12.00pm. Some people bring sandwiches,and some people have school dinners,which cost 60p per day.We have afternoon break at 2.15pm.We go home at 3.00pm. When I get home, I play outside or watch T.V.At 5.00 o'clock pm I have tea.I have sausages,mash and beans. At eight I go to bed.
